I like how we have all agreed that coffee mugs are a "fun" drinking vessel that gets to have a cute cartoon etc. on it. Whiskey glasses, wine glasses are all serious, but in the coffee mug you get a lot of leeway in terms of zaniness. One I'm using rn has a Claude Monet painting.
This is a very Gravantian post

Like you go into someone's house and he makes you a cup of coffee in a Snoopy the dog mug. Always a fun experience. Definitely my favorite part of kitchenware. Most recent one I got as gift was from someone who had been in Venice, has the covered bridge there and St. Mark's lion.

Younger bro at the gym stayed for an hour after he was done with his workout just to hang out with me and ask me gym stuff. Has the same lifting quirks like me like being arm dominant and a lot stronger in narrow grip bench/pulldowns, taking 5 minutes between sets, making noises,

If you have the same rugged build like us with huge forearms and stocky body you should not torture yourself trying to do exercises the normal way with wide grip, you can just do what others would call a close grip bench as your default to get as strong as possible... it works...
It's the upper extreme imo but anything less on heavy lifts and my performance goes to zero

Surprising amount of paranormal stories from toilets/bathrooms. People sighting ghosts of people who took their lives in the building, seeing stuff outside from windows. I guess it's what Tanizaki said "In Praise of Shadows", it's a somewhat contemplative spot of spiritual repose

Even in its worst form the toilet is still an opportunity to free your mind a bit and step outside regulated time and space for a minute. It's also why people get good insights on the toilet a lot of the time. Something coming outside of regular life will be easier to see there.
